<collectingRegion box="[307,414,942,968]" country="Bahamas" name="South Eleuthera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Eleuthera</collectingRegion>
Island; 
<date box="[508,669,942,969]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2013-04-15">15 April 2013</date>
; S. B. Johnson. Host: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[923,1055,942,968]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Cyrtopholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[923,1055,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cyrtopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<emphasis box="[1094,1192,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">bonhotei</emphasis>
(F. O. P.-Cambridge) (
<taxonomicName box="[205,376,978,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult female. The wasp pulled the paralyzed tarantula backwards on the ground, grasping the base of its left foreleg with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, S. B." box="[678,840,1014,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref82697" refString="Johnson, S. B. (2013) Wild Bahamas. Available from: https: // m. facebook. com / BahamianWildlife / photos / a. 566011986805811.1073741828.493872100686467 / 566322856774724 /? type = 3 &amp; source = 54 (accessed 30 June 2017)" type="url" year="2013">Johnson 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,906,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<collectingCountry box="[151,232,1050,1076]" name="Haiti" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">HAITI</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[242,450,1050,1077]" country="Haiti" name="Ouest" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ouest Department</collectingRegion>
, Thomazeau; 
<date box="[607,809,1050,1076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2017-02-17">17 February 2017</date>
; E. Russell (SierraSunrise). Host: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1194,1326,1050,1076]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Cyrtopholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1194,1326,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cyrtopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<emphasis box="[1363,1436,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">cursor</emphasis>
(Ausserer) (Dominican stripeknee tarantula) (
<taxonomicName box="[708,879,1086,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp stood by the paralyzed tarantula as it laid on the ground near its burrow, dorsal side upward (
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, E." box="[1091,1240,1122,1148]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref94744" refString="Russell, E. (2017) Tarantula hawk &amp; tarantula. Available from: https: // www. flickr. com / photos / eddingrid / 32831788501 / in / album- 72157671936950665 / (accessed 16 November 2018)" type="url" year="2017">Russell 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,906,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
