: Saint John Island, Coral Bay; 
<date box="[777,982,1158,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2020-02-17">17 February 2020</date>
; P. Offermanns (SUPstjohn). Host: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Cyrtopholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cyrtopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<emphasis box="[324,461,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">bartholomei</emphasis>
(Latreille) (St. Thomas grey-striped spider) (
<taxonomicName box="[967,1138,1194,1221]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. A short video shows the wasp dragging the paralyzed tarantula backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping the base of its left pedipalp with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation author="Offermanns, P." box="[840,1043,1266,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref89669" refString="Offermanns, P. (2020) Island life ... (tarantula hawk vs. tarantula-round 1). Available from: https: // www. facebook. com / watch /? v = 241325673542341 (accessed 23 April 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Offermanns 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
